         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">20/4/88 ¶  ¶ The Richardsonia, sent by you, dear Mr Dean, ¶  I had a few years ago from Mr Betche also, and (if I rightly remember) I referred it then, as our friend Dr Woolls now, also to the genus R...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.04.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Deane</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 576, folder 30, series 4, MS 610 Deane family papers, National Library of Australia, Canberra.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">P. PS. C. 22/8/08.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>20/4/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Richardsonia, sent by you, dear Mr Dean,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">sic.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I had a few years ago from Mr Betche also, and (if I rightly remember) I referred it then, as our friend Dr Woolls now, also to the genus Richardsonia, expressing the probability, that, this plant might have been introduced from South-America. Mr Betche's specimens were imperfect, and thus laid aside for subsequent study from better material, in connection with South American evidently allied congeners; but the work in the department here is so varied, and usually so overwhelming, that, when once a plant is laid aside, it may not come before me for a long time again. I will now see, whether I can identify it with any species from South-America. It is quite possible, that I may have since passed it on some occasion as the Sherardia arvensis, which I know well from Europe, and of which I had the genuine plant repeatedly from Near Port Jackson,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW.</p>
               </note> as I have often to use the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">late</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">evening</hi>
               </seg>-<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">hours</hi>
               </seg> to name plants for correspondents, when I may be tired after a heavy days work and my eyes very fatigued</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">It seems the intended ascent of Mt Seaview<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW.</p>
               </note> is not to be realised this season.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">x-ref to earlier letters and add note re fate of ascent to an early letter.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is seldom,<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">no comma, looks like a mark on the page.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> the Lythr. hyssopif<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Lythrum hyssopifolia</seg> L.</p>
               </note> is found with such large flowers.</p>
         </div>
